<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="affair-n">affair <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'feə(r)/    美 /ə'fer/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>事务</strong></h4>
<p>important personal, business, national, etc. matters：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the Ministry of <strong>Foreign Affairs</strong> 
外交部</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>current / international / business affairs</strong>
时事/国际事务/商业事务</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[常用单数] 事件；事情</strong></h4>
<p>an event or situation：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the Watergate affair 
水门事件</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She wanted the celebration to be a simple <strong>family affair</strong>.
她希望庆祝活动仅限于家人参加。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>暧昧关系；通奸；私通：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>have an affair with sb</strong> 
与某人有暧昧关系</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a love affair</strong>
风流韵事；酷爱；热爱</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="state-of-affairs">state of affairs</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[正式用语] 情况；局势；事态：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The state of affairs should no longer be ignored. 
局势不容忽视。</p></div>

<h3 id="matter-affair-event">辨析 matter, affair, event</h3>
<p>三者都有“事情”之意。<br />
<strong>matter</strong>  通常指客观存在的或有待处理的问题，常用于“a matter of”结构中。
<strong>affair ** 可用于描述严肃认真的公共或政治“事务”；也可描述与个人生活密切相关的“小事”。
</strong>event ** 通常指“重要事件”、“大事”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The election was the main event of 2016.
那次选举是2016年的大事。</p></div></div>